						<div class="postbody">I was under the impression, perhaps mistakenly, that the CPU address bus was used to load instructions from the program in ROM. If that's what it does, I want it to perform its intended function.<br /><br />Edit:<br /><br />To answer more directly: If the CPU address bus is used to load instructions from ROM, then I do not want addresses unrelated to the actual program to show up on that bus, in order to prevent the NES from loading garbage instructions.<br /><br />Video out is disposable, but the stored program is not.</div>

